headline: Intuit CFO Sandeep Aujla to Present at the Jefferies Public Technology Conference
summary: MOUNTAIN VIEW, Calif., May 23, 2025--Intuit Inc. (Nasdaq: INTU), the global financial technology platform that makes Intuit TurboTax, Credit Karma, QuickBooks, and Mailchimp, announced today that Sandeep Aujla, chief financial officer, will present at the Jefferies Public Technology Conference on May 28, 2025.

headline: Nuclear rally, Deckers Outdoor, Intuit gains: Trending Tickers
summary: Nuclear energy stocks Oklo (OKLO), Constellation Energy (CEG), Nano Nuclear Energy (NNE), and NuScale Power (SMR) are rallying as President Trump signs an executive order to ease regulations around nuclear reactor development. Catch Yahoo Finance's interview with Nano Nuclear Energy founder, executive chairman, and president Jay Yu on the nuclear energy landscape. Shares of shoe company Deckers Outdoor (DECK) continue to tumble ahead of Friday's market close after the company did not provide full-year guidance. Intuit (INTU) holds onto stock gains after reporting earnings on Thursday, on pace to close at a record high. Watch Yahoo Finance's interview with Intuit CFO Sandeep Aujla. headline: Stellantis, Apple fall on tariff threats, Intuit jumps on earnings
summary: Early morning Truth Social posts from US President Donald Trump are rattling markets. Shares of Stellantis (STLA) are slipping after Trump posted that he was "recommending a straight 50% Tariff on the European Union, starting on June 1, 2025." Apple (AAPL) shares are also sliding following a Trump post where the president threatened a 25% tariff on iPhones that are sold in the US but not made in the US. Shares of Intuit (INTU) are rising after posting better-than-expected Q3 results and raising its full-year guidance. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Morning Brief here.
